issue.title: Can't compile bitcoin for SmartOS - recipe for target 'consensus/libbitcoinconsensus_la-merkle.lo' failed

events.body: It looks like int8_t and char are the same type on your system, while the code assumes they're different. I'm not sure how we should deal with that.
Is this a compiler issue and would recompiling a later version of g++ get over the issue? Which version do you recommend to get over this issue?
@stacepellegrino could you re-open this? We can close it when a fix is merged.
Reopened till the fix is merged.
